(28, 23, 'subscription to research professional africa platform for funding opportunities', 'subscription to research professional africa platform for funding opportunities', '<p>This is to kindly inform you that the University of Dar es Salaam has finally managed to subscribe to the Research Professional Africa Platform for one year starting 22<sup>nd</sup>November 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform allows UDSM researchers to access the latest and up to-date information about Research Funding opportunities from different funders and sponsors around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Directorate of Research and Publication is encouraging all University of Dar es Salaam researchers to take full advantage of this facility which can be accessed through the following link:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.researchprofessional.com/" target="_blank">http://www.researchprofessional.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform allows for users at the UDSM to create their own accounts by doing self-registration and then signing in. Should you require assistance in creating an account, please contact the DVC-Research Office System Administrator at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:dvc-rke@admin.udsm.ac.tz">dvc-rke@admin.udsm.ac.tz</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Training sessions</strong>&nbsp;may be arranged on request</p>\r\n', '<p>This is to kindly inform you that the University of Dar es Salaam has finally managed to subscribe to the Research Professional Africa Platform for one year starting 22<sup>nd</sup>November 2016.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform allows UDSM researchers to access the latest and up to-date information about Research Funding opportunities from different funders and sponsors around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Directorate of Research and Publication is encouraging all University of Dar es Salaam researchers to take full advantage of this facility which can be accessed through the following link:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://www.researchprofessional.com/" target="_blank">http://www.researchprofessional.com</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The platform allows for users at the UDSM to create their own accounts by doing self-registration and then signing in. Should you require assistance in creating an account, please contact the DVC-Research Office System Administrator at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:dvc-rke@admin.udsm.ac.tz">dvc-rke@admin.udsm.ac.tz</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Training sessions</strong>&nbsp;may be arranged on request</p>\r\n', 'UNIT23_subscription to research professional africa platform for funding opportunities.pdf', '2017-11-15 12:37:04', '2017-11-15 12:37:04', 1, 0, '/institutes/ims/announcements/subscription-to-research-professional-africa-platform-for-funding-opportunities'),
(29, 23, 'appointment', 'appointment', '<p>This is to inform the University of Dar es Salaam Community and the public that, in exercise of the powers vested upon him under section 55 of the Universities Act, Cap. 346 R.E. 2002, as reads together with Article 7 (3) of the University of Dar es Salaam Charter 2007, and Rule 9 of the University of Dar es Salaam Rules 2007, the Chancellor, H.E. Dr. Jakaya Mrisho Kikwete has appointed <strong>Dr Margareth S. Kyewalyanga </strong>to the position of <strong>Director of the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS), </strong>for the remainder of the 2015/16 - 2017/18 Triennium. The appointment is effective from 1<sup>st</sup> August 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr Kyewalyanga is a Senior Lecturer in the Department of Marine Biology and Resources Management and before this appointment she was the Head of this Department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We congratulate Dr. Kyewalyanga for the appointment</p>\r\n', '<p>This is to inform the University of Dar es Salaam Community and the public that, in exercise of the powers vested upon him under section 55 of the Universities Act, Cap. 346 R.E. 2002, as reads together with Article 7 (3) of the University of Dar es Salaam Charter 2007, and Rule 9 of the University of Dar es Salaam Rules 2007, the Chancellor, H.E. Dr. Jakaya Mrisho Kikwete has appointed <strong>Dr Margareth S. Kyewalyanga </strong>to the position of <strong>Director of the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS), </strong>for the remainder of the 2015/16 - 2017/18 Triennium. The appointment is effective from 1<sup>st</sup> August 2017.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr Kyewalyanga is a Senior Lecturer in the Department of Marine Biology and Resources Management and before this appointment she was the Head of this Department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We congratulate Dr. Kyewalyanga for the appointment</p>\r\n', NULL, '2017-11-15 14:22:12', '2017-11-15 14:22:12', 1, 0, '/institutes/ims/announcements/appointment'),
(30, 23, 'submission of abstracts for the 10th wiomsa scientific symposium: online system activated', 'submission of abstracts for the 10th wiomsa scientific symposium: online system activated', '<p>Abstracts are invited on any topic related to coastal and marine environment of the region. See the Symposium Themes from http://symposium.wiomsa.org/programme/. Priority will be given to multi-/trans-/interdisciplinary abstracts. Please note the following important points: 1. Abstracts must be in English as that is the official language of the Symposium. 2. The abstract submission site will not accept abstracts of more than 310 words. Abstracts should provide a brief statement of the problem, the methodology, the results and the conclusion. The abstract should be submitted in plain text only; without the inclusion of tables, graphs, images, etc. All abstracts will be reviewed for merit and relevance. 3. Abstracts by students should be indicated by the word &quot;STUDENT&quot; (in uppercase) at the start of the abstract otherwise they will not be considered for the student competitions. 4. Please do not include the word &ldquo;ABSTRACT&rdquo; as part of the title/ heading when submitting texts of your abstracts. 5. Do not use hard returns/open lines in the abstract. It should be one paragraph without line breaks. Logging in for Returning Authors We are using the same system as the 2015 symposium for submission of abstracts. If you are a returning author (submitting an abstract) please use the same profile/login/password as previously. If you have forgotten those details, please log onto http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS and follow the instructions to receive a new password. Please try and avoid creating duplicate profiles. PLEASE CHECK THAT YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS IS CORRECTLY LISTED IN YOUR PROFILE. (check under &quot;My Profile&quot; link on the right of the page) New Authors For new authors, please follow the instructions below: Instructions for registering on the abstracting website: 1. Go to: http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS; 2. Navigate to &quot;Account&quot; tab on the top menu; 3. Populate your profile with information 4. Right at the bottom: &quot;Create account as&quot; - tick Author; 5. Ignore &quot;Reviewer&quot; tick. 6. Submit. You will receive an email to confirm your registration. 7. Once registered, please log in and submit a new abstract. Abstracts must be submitted online at http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS no later than 28th April 2017.</p>\r\n', '<p>Abstracts are invited on any topic related to coastal and marine environment of the region. See the Symposium Themes from http://symposium.wiomsa.org/programme/. Priority will be given to multi-/trans-/interdisciplinary abstracts. Please note the following important points: 1. Abstracts must be in English as that is the official language of the Symposium. 2. The abstract submission site will not accept abstracts of more than 310 words. Abstracts should provide a brief statement of the problem, the methodology, the results and the conclusion. The abstract should be submitted in plain text only; without the inclusion of tables, graphs, images, etc. All abstracts will be reviewed for merit and relevance. 3. Abstracts by students should be indicated by the word &quot;STUDENT&quot; (in uppercase) at the start of the abstract otherwise they will not be considered for the student competitions. 4. Please do not include the word &ldquo;ABSTRACT&rdquo; as part of the title/ heading when submitting texts of your abstracts. 5. Do not use hard returns/open lines in the abstract. It should be one paragraph without line breaks. Logging in for Returning Authors We are using the same system as the 2015 symposium for submission of abstracts. If you are a returning author (submitting an abstract) please use the same profile/login/password as previously. If you have forgotten those details, please log onto http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS and follow the instructions to receive a new password. Please try and avoid creating duplicate profiles. PLEASE CHECK THAT YOUR EMAIL ADDRESS IS CORRECTLY LISTED IN YOUR PROFILE. (check under &quot;My Profile&quot; link on the right of the page) New Authors For new authors, please follow the instructions below: Instructions for registering on the abstracting website: 1. Go to: http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS; 2. Navigate to &quot;Account&quot; tab on the top menu; 3. Populate your profile with information 4. Right at the bottom: &quot;Create account as&quot; - tick Author; 5. Ignore &quot;Reviewer&quot; tick. 6. Submit. You will receive an email to confirm your registration. 7. Once registered, please log in and submit a new abstract. Abstracts must be submitted online at http://abstract.wiomsa.org/index.php/wiomsa/10WSS no later than 28th April 2017.</p>\r\n', NULL, '2017-11-15 14:24:32', '2017-11-15 14:24:32', 1, 0, '/institutes/ims/announcements/submission-of-abstracts-for-the-10th-wiomsa-scientific-symposium:-online-system-activated'),
(31, 22, 'african climate change fellowship program', 'african climate change fellowship program', '<p><strong>AFRICAN CLIMATE CHANGE FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM (ACCFP) &ndash; PHASE III</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CULMINATION CONFERENCE: 30TH - 31ST JANUARY, 2017</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>THEME</strong><br />\r\n&lsquo;Advancing Science to Address Climate Change Challenges for Sustainable Development in Africa&rsquo;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>AFRICAN CLIMATE CHANGE FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM (ACCFP) &ndash; PHASE III</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>CULMINATION CONFERENCE: 30TH - 31ST JANUARY, 2017</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>THEME</strong><br />\r\n<strong><em>Advancing Science to Address Climate Change Challenges for Sustainable Development in Africa</em></strong></p>\r\n', 'UNIT22_african climate change fellowship program.pdf', '2017-11-16 10:41:58', '2017-11-16 10:46:32', 1, 0, '/institutes/ira/announcements/african-climate-change-fellowship-program'),
(32, 22, 'short course on climate change and sustainable development', 'short course on climate change and sustainable development', '<p><em><strong>SHORT COURSE ON &lsquo;CLIMATE CHANGE AND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT&rsquo; 14th- 25th November 2016</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) of the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM) wishes to announce a two-week short course on &lsquo;CLIMATE CHANGE AND SUSTAINABLE<br />\r\nDEVELOPMENT&rsquo; which is organized under the African Climate Change Fellowship Program (ACCFP). As a regional capacity building program, the ACCFP offers experiential learning, education, and research and training opportunities to African professionals, researchers and graduate students to develop their capabilities for advancing and applying knowledge for climate change adaptation in Africa. ACCFP is jointly administered by the Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) of the University of Dar es Salaam (i.e. the ACCFP Secretariat) and the International START based in Washington DC with funding from the International Development Research Centre (IDRC), Canada. The purpose of the short course is to develop capacity of the participants for advancing and applying scientific knowledge for climate change adaptation by learning the following modules:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and water resources;</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and gender;</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and green growth; and</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>economics of climate change adaptation.</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Targeted course participants</strong><br />\r\nThe short course on climate change and sustainable development targets practitioners and nonpractitioners working with government and non-government institutions on water resources, gender, wildlife, forestry, agriculture, fisheries, land, and other several environmental and socioeconomic related fields.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Language</strong><br />\r\nThe course will be conducted in English. Participants are supposed to possess basic English proficiency to be able to follow the course and be actively involved in the training activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course fees</strong><br />\r\nThe course fee for both local and international participants will be 1,000,000 Tanzanian Shillings (US$ 500) for two weeks. The fee will cover the course material, lunch, refreshments and one day field visit to a selected site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Training venue</strong><br />\r\nThe short course will be conducted at the Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) at the University of Dar es Salaam in Tanzania.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration and payments</strong><br />\r\nTo register for a course please download and fill the application form found at the ACCFP Website (www.accfp.org) and send the filled form to the <strong>ACCFP Secretariat</strong> at IRA through accfp2@gmail.com; copy to Rosalyne Baddoo at naanorkor27@gmail.com and Dr. Elikana Kalumanga at ekalumanga@yahoo.com before 13th November 2016. The payments should be done through the CRDB Bank (Tanzania) -UDSM Branch. Account name: UDSM IRA ACCFP PROJECT. Account number <strong>0250396193300</strong> for US$ and <strong>0150396193300</strong> for Tshs. Swift code CORUTZTZ.</p>\r\n', '<p><em><strong>SHORT COURSE ON &lsquo;CLIMATE CHANGE AND SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT&rsquo; 14th- 25th November 2016</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) of the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM) wishes to announce a two-week short course on &lsquo;CLIMATE CHANGE AND SUSTAINABLE<br />\r\nDEVELOPMENT&rsquo; which is organized under the African Climate Change Fellowship Program (ACCFP). As a regional capacity building program, the ACCFP offers experiential learning, education, and research and training opportunities to African professionals, researchers and graduate students to develop their capabilities for advancing and applying knowledge for climate change adaptation in Africa. ACCFP is jointly administered by the Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) of the University of Dar es Salaam (i.e. the ACCFP Secretariat) and the International START based in Washington DC with funding from the International Development Research Centre (IDRC), Canada. The purpose of the short course is to develop capacity of the participants for advancing and applying scientific knowledge for climate change adaptation by learning the following modules:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and water resources;</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and gender;</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>climate change and green growth; and</em></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong><em>economics of climate change adaptation.</em></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Targeted course participants</strong><br />\r\nThe short course on climate change and sustainable development targets practitioners and nonpractitioners working with government and non-government institutions on water resources, gender, wildlife, forestry, agriculture, fisheries, land, and other several environmental and socioeconomic related fields.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Language</strong><br />\r\nThe course will be conducted in English. Participants are supposed to possess basic English proficiency to be able to follow the course and be actively involved in the training activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Course fees</strong><br />\r\nThe course fee for both local and international participants will be 1,000,000 Tanzanian Shillings (US$ 500) for two weeks. The fee will cover the course material, lunch, refreshments and one day field visit to a selected site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Training venue</strong><br />\r\nThe short course will be conducted at the Institute of Resource Assessment (IRA) at the University of Dar es Salaam in Tanzania.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Registration and payments</strong><br />\r\nTo register for a course please download and fill the application form found at the ACCFP Website (www.accfp.org) and send the filled form to the <strong>ACCFP Secretariat</strong> at IRA through accfp2@gmail.com; copy to Rosalyne Baddoo at naanorkor27@gmail.com and Dr. Elikana Kalumanga at ekalumanga@yahoo.com before 13th November 2016. The payments should be done through the CRDB Bank (Tanzania) -UDSM Branch. Account name: UDSM IRA ACCFP PROJECT. Account number <strong>0250396193300</strong> for US$ and <strong>0150396193300</strong> for Tshs. Swift code CORUTZTZ.</p>\r\n', 'UNIT22_short course on climate change and sustainable development.pdf', '2017-11-16 10:49:23', '2017-11-16 10:58:41', 1, 0, '/institutes/ira/announcements/short-course-on-climate-change-and-sustainable-development'),
