(82, 'History of the Institute', 'Historia ya Taasisi', '<p>The importance of conducting research and training in marine sciences dates back to 1965 when the Faculty of Science of the then Dar es Salaam College of East Africa introduced a course in Marine Biology. The need for creating an institution with the mandate to conduct research and training in marine sciences was pointed out in 1974 during an International Conference on Marine Resource Development in Eastern Africa. The conference, which was organized by the Department of Zoology and Marine Biology of the University of Dar es Salaam, had a primary objective of assessing the need and potential for marine resources development in Eastern Africa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the major deliberations of the conference was establishment of an Institute of Marine Resource Development. This recommendation was taken-up seriously by the University and the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS) was established on 17th October 1978 under the University of Dar es Salaam Act No. 12 of 1970. The establishment of the Institute of Marine Sciences was tabled and approved by the University Council on 18th August 1978 and later endorsed by the Government through the University of Dar es Salaam (Establishment of Institute of Marine Sciences) Order, 1979 (Government Notice No. 34 published on 16th March 1979)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the planning of the physical facilities of the Institute was under consideration, the East African Community (EAC) broke-up. The community had a research organization based on Zanzibar known as the East African Marine Fisheries Research Organization (EAMFRO), which was mainly dealing with fisheries research. Since the activities of the EAMFRO were partly similar to those of the proposed Institute, it was decided that the former should be a nucleus to the latter, and subsequently the premises were transferred to the University of Dar es Salaam. IMS is still based in the same premises. However, construction of the institute headquarters is currently being undertaken at a more spacious area at Buyu, about 13 km south of the Stone Town of Zanzibar.</p>\r\n', '<p>The importance of conducting research and training in marine sciences dates back to 1965 when the Faculty of Science of the then Dar es Salaam College of East Africa introduced a course in Marine Biology. The need for creating an institution with the mandate to conduct research and training in marine sciences was pointed out in 1974 during an International Conference on Marine Resource Development in Eastern Africa. The conference, which was organized by the Department of Zoology and Marine Biology of the University of Dar es Salaam, had a primary objective of assessing the need and potential for marine resources development in Eastern Africa</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the major deliberations of the conference was establishment of an Institute of Marine Resource Development. This recommendation was taken-up seriously by the University and the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS) was established on 17th October 1978 under the University of Dar es Salaam Act No. 12 of 1970. The establishment of the Institute of Marine Sciences was tabled and approved by the University Council on 18th August 1978 and later endorsed by the Government through the University of Dar es Salaam (Establishment of Institute of Marine Sciences) Order, 1979 (Government Notice No. 34 published on 16th March 1979)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the planning of the physical facilities of the Institute was under consideration, the East African Community (EAC) broke-up. The community had a research organization based on Zanzibar known as the East African Marine Fisheries Research Organization (EAMFRO), which was mainly dealing with fisheries research. Since the activities of the EAMFRO were partly similar to those of the proposed Institute, it was decided that the former should be a nucleus to the latter, and subsequently the premises were transferred to the University of Dar es Salaam. IMS is still based in the same premises. However, construction of the institute headquarters is currently being undertaken at a more spacious area at Buyu, about 13 km south of the Stone Town of Zanzibar.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 'institutes/ims/history-of-the-institute', '2017-11-13 08:38:21', 1, 23, ''),
(83, 'PhD. Kiswahili ', 'PhD. Kiswahili ', '<p>PhD. Kiswahili</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Masomo katika programu hii hutolewa kwa namna mbili. PhD kwa Tamrini na Tasnifu.PhD kwa Tamrini hutolewa kwa muda wa miaka minne na PhD kwa Tasnifu hutolewa kwa muda wa miaka mitatu. Ilikudahiliwa katika programu hizi mwombaji anapaswa kuwa amesoma Kiswahili au masomo yanayoendana na umahiri. Lugha inayotumika kufundishia na kuandika ripoti ya utafiti kwa programu zote ni Kiswahili</p>\r\n', '<p>PhD. Kiswahili</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Masomo katika programu hii hutolewa kwa namna mbili. PhD kwa Tamrini na Tasnifu.PhD kwa Tamrini hutolewa kwa muda wa miaka minne na PhD kwa Tasnifu hutolewa kwa muda wa miaka mitatu. Ilikudahiliwa katika programu hizi mwombaji anapaswa kuwa amesoma Kiswahili au masomo yanayoendana na umahiri. Lugha inayotumika kufundishia na kuandika ripoti ya utafiti kwa programu zote ni Kiswahili</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, '', '/institutes/iks/phd.-kiswahili', '2017-11-24 12:04:54', 1, 20, NULL),
(84, 'Research and Publications', 'Research and Publications', '<p>Currently, research activities at the Institute are guided by the University of Dar es Salaam Research Agenda which is cascaded to the IDS. The Tanzania Journal of Development Studies is a flagship journal owned and hosted by the IDS. The Institute is undertaking researches around the following broad thematic areas: &bull; Development Policies &bull; Governance, Democracy and Democratization &bull; Science, Technology, Innovation and Industrialisation &bull; Rural and Urban Development &bull; Population, Health, and Environment &bull; Gender and Development &bull; Peace and Conflicts Resolution &bull; Regional Cooperation, Integration and Globalization</p>\r\n', '<p>Currently, research activities at the Institute are guided by the University of Dar es Salaam Research Agenda which is cascaded to the IDS. The Tanzania Journal of Development Studies is a flagship journal owned and hosted by the IDS. The Institute is undertaking researches around the following broad thematic areas:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Development Policies</li>\r\n	<li>Governance, Democracy and Democratization</li>\r\n	<li>Science, Technology, Innovation and Industrialisation</li>\r\n	<li>Rural and Urban Development</li>\r\n	<li>Population, Health, and Environment</li>\r\n	<li>Gender and Development&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Peace and Conflicts Resolution</li>\r\n	<li>Regional Cooperation, Integration and Globalization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 'institutes/ids/#/research-and-publications/research-and-publications', '2017-11-13 08:55:35', 1, 21, 'institutes/ids/#/research-and-publications/'),
(85, 'M.A. Kiswahili', 'M.A. Kiswahili', '<p>M.A. Kiswahili</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hii ni shahada ua umahiri ambayo hutolewa kwa Tamrini na Tasnifu katika Isimu na Fasihi kwa muda wa miezi 18 (Tamrini na Tasnifu); na miezi 24 (kwa Tasnifu pekee). Ili kujiunga na programu hii mbali na sifa za jumla za Chuo Kikuu cha Dar es Salaam, mwombaji anapaswa kuwa amefaulu masomo ya Kiswahili katika shahada za awali kwa WAKIA (GPA) isiyopungua 3.0 kwa kozi za Kiswahili.</p>\r\n', '<p>M.A. Kiswahili</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hii ni shahada ua umahiri ambayo hutolewa kwa Tamrini na Tasnifu katika Isimu na Fasihi kwa muda wa miezi 18 (Tamrini na Tasnifu); na miezi 24 (kwa Tasnifu pekee). Ili kujiunga na programu hii mbali na sifa za jumla za Chuo Kikuu cha Dar es Salaam, mwombaji anapaswa kuwa amefaulu masomo ya Kiswahili katika shahada za awali kwa WAKIA (GPA) isiyopungua 3.0 kwa kozi za Kiswahili.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL, '<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WfRSaMfO6xw?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '/institutes/iks/m.a.-kiswahili', '2017-11-28 07:49:35', 1, 20, NULL),
(89, 'B.A. Kiswahili', 'B.A. Kiswahili', '<p>Ni shahada ya awali ambayo hutolewa katika muda wa miaka mitatu. Katika shahada hii, kozi mbalimbali za Isimu na Fasihi hutolewa. Masharti ya jumla ya udahili ya Chuo Kikuu huzingatiwa. Hata hivyo ili mwombaji adahiliwe katika programu ya B.A (kiswahili) anapaswa, pamoja na masomo mengine, awe amesoma somo la Kiswahili kidato cha tano na sita na kufaulu kwa wastani wa angalau alama D au awe na sifa zinazofanana na hizo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madhuminiya shahada ya BA Kiswahili nikuwawezesha wanafunzi kupatamaarifanamsingikatikaisimunafasihiya Kiswahili, zitazowawezesha kuchambua, kuelezeanakuchanganuanadharia, muundowamatumiziyalughanafasihiya Kiswahili nahivyokuwafanyawatambuemwingilianouliopobainayalughanafasihi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aidha shahada ya BA Kiswahili itawapatiawanafunzimisinginauelewampananawakinawalugha, fasihinautamaduniwawaswahili, stadizauchunguzinachanganuziwalughanafasihiwaKiswahili,&nbsp; nastadizamawasiliano, uandishinauchapishajikatika Kiswahili.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Madhumunimahususi</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kufundishakozizaisimuya Kiswahili zikiwamo; isimusauti, isimumaumbo, isimumiundo, isimu maana, isimu jamii na isimu tumizi ilikuwapatia wanafunzi maarifa ya msingikatikaisimuya Kiswahili;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kufundishakozizafasihiya Kiswahili, ikiwamo: fasihisimulizi, fasihiandishi, mawasilianonauandishikatika Kiswahili nahivyokuwapawanafunziujuziwamsinginautambuzikuhusumwingilianouliopobainayalugha, fasihinajamii; kuandaawataalamuambaowatajfundishataalumaza Kiswahili kwenyengazizaelimuyasekondarinavyuo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuandaawataalamuwatakofanyakazikatikavyombovyahabari, mashirikayauchapishaji, idarazaserikali, mashirikayakimataifa, namaeneomenginehusika;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuaandaawataalamuwauwanjawautumiziwateknolojiayakompyutakatikautafitiwaufundishajiwalugha.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Malengo</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Malengomakuuyaprogramuya shahada ya BA Kiswahilini :kuwawezeshawanafunzikupatamisingiyakuelezea, kuichambuanakuihakikilughailikuwanaufahamukuhusuisimunafasihiyalughaya Kiswahili.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Misingihiisiyotuitawawezeshawanafunzikuthamininakufahamuuwezowakiisimunakiifasihiwalughayao, likini Zaidi itawafanyawawenauwezompanawamatumizimbalimbaliyalugha. Aidha, kupitiakatika BA Kiswahili wanafunziwatapatastadinambunuzakuwawakalimani bora, wafasirimahiri, nawaandishiwamakala bora zakitaalumazinazohusulughanafasihiya Kiswahili. Aidha, watapatauwelewampanakuusujamiiyaowenyewenamazingirayake;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuwapatiawanafunzimbinuzauandishiwakubuni, nambinuzamsingizaukarimaninatafsiri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuwapatiawanafunzimaarifanastadizamawasilianonauchapishaji</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuwapatiawanafunzimaalifayamsingikuhusuutumiajiwatekinolojiayakompyutakatikautafitinaufundishajiwalughanafasihi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>maarubu</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>sababuzakuanzishaprogramuza BA Kiswahili ni</p>\r\n\r\n<p>kuwawezeshawanafunzikuzikuzataalumaza Kiswahili nakuzifanyazistawikwakutumiamafunzowatakayoyapatakuaziakatikangaziyadigriiya kwanza.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kuandaawanafunziwatakaowezakusomamasomoyauzamili (umahilinauzamivu) katikaisimu, fasihi, nauchapishajikwa Kiswahili.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ilikiswahilikiwelughayakitaaluma, tunahitajiwataalamuwatakaofanyakatikavyombovyahabari, mashiirikayauchapishaji, halimashaurimbalimbaliza Kiswahili katika Afrika masharikinakati, nakatikatumeya Kiswahili ya Afrika masharikiiliyoanzishwahivikaribuni. BA Kiswahili itaanzishamchakatowautaalamishajiwatuhawakwakuzingatiamuktadhawasasawamaendeleowateknolojiayahabarinamawasiliano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mojawapoyanjiazamsingizakupimamaaendeleoyalughaniuwezo wake wakuelezanakufafanuamashwalayakisayansinakiteknolojia. Lughaambayoinaishiakatikakuelezamaasualayakawaidatuhubakikuwanyumatudaimahatakamaidadiwawatumiaji wake nikubwa. BA Kiswahili inaanzishwailikuandaawanafunziwatakaoletamaaendeleonamageuazihayakatikalughaya Kiswahili.</p>\r\n', '<p>Ni shahada ya awali ambayo hutolewa katika muda wa miaka mitatu. Katika shahada hii, kozi mbali