(137, 'Global Environmental Change', 'Global Environmental Change', '<p>IRA is the leading institution in issues related to environmental assessments which includes Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA), Strategic Environmental Assessments (SEA) and Environmental Management Systems (EMS-ISO 14000). IRA offers advice on issues related to</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategic environmental advice for all stages of project life cycle</li>\r\n	<li>Compliance advice and auditing in terms of environmental best practices</li>\r\n	<li>Renewable and non-renewable energy projects appraisal and implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="environmental assessment" src="http://www.ira.udsm.ac.tz/images/stories/Home/environmental-assessment.jpg" /></p>\r\n', '<p>IRA is the leading institution in issues related to environmental assessments which includes Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA), Strategic Environmental Assessments (SEA) and Environmental Management Systems (EMS-ISO 14000). IRA offers advice on issues related to</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strategic environmental advice for all stages of project life cycle</li>\r\n	<li>Compliance advice and auditing in terms of environmental best practices</li>\r\n	<li>Renewable and non-renewable energy projects appraisal and implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="environmental assessment" src="http://www.ira.udsm.ac.tz/images/stories/Home/environmental-assessment.jpg" /></p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 'institutes/ira/global-environmental-change', '2017-11-14 10:19:48', 1, 22, ''),
(138, 'Ecological Assessment', 'Ecological Assessment', '<p>IRA uses an ecosystem approach to characterize the nature and magnitude of ecological changes and its implications to humans (e.g., residents, workers, recreational visitors) and ecological receptors (e.g., birds, fish, wildlife) from pollutants, land use changes and other stressors, acting on the environment. Natural resources managers use this information to help them decide how to protect humans and the environment. In 2008 IRA implemented an Integrated Ecosystem Assessment of the Livingstone Mountain Ranges in Mbinga District, Tanzania. The program was implemented as a pilot phase towards the implementation of the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MA) in the Tanzanian context</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Ecological Assessments" src="http://www.ira.udsm.ac.tz/images/stories/Home/Ecological-Assessments.jpg" /></p>\r\n', '<p>IRA uses an ecosystem approach to characterize the nature and magnitude of ecological changes and its implications to humans (e.g., residents, workers, recreational visitors) and ecological receptors (e.g., birds, fish, wildlife) from pollutants, land use changes and other stressors, acting on the environment. Natural resources managers use this information to help them decide how to protect humans and the environment. In 2008 IRA implemented an Integrated Ecosystem Assessment of the Livingstone Mountain Ranges in Mbinga District, Tanzania. The program was implemented as a pilot phase towards the implementation of the Millennium Ecosystem Assessment (MA) in the Tanzanian context</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Ecological Assessments" src="http://www.ira.udsm.ac.tz/images/stories/Home/Ecological-Assessments.jpg" /></p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 'institutes/ira/ecological-assessment', '2017-11-14 10:14:15', 1, 22, ''),
(139, 'history-department', 'history-department', '<p><strong>History </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Department of History</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Year of Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>1964, One of the oldest Departments of theUniversityofDar es Salaam.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Vision</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>To become an internationally recognized History Department and Centre for research, teaching, consultancy and publication.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Mission</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>To enable students to become best historically-minded individuals (informed decision makers and advisers) and become highly competitive in the global market of research, academic excellence and governance.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Number of academic staff</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>21</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Degree Program(s) offered</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>One Degree Program</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Levels of degree e.g. BA, MA</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>B.A. M.A. (by thesis, and by coursework and dissertation) PhD (by thesis)</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Sample of the courses offered</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>History ofTanzania;Africaand World Religions; Neo-colonialism and Revolutionary Movements; African Environmental History; War and Warfare; Political Economy of USA; and Urban and Population Histories of Tanzania</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Entrance requirements</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li>B.A. History &ndash; at least three A-Level principal passes, at least three Ds, one them must be from History</li>\r\n				<li>M.A. History &ndash; an undergraduate G.P.A. of&nbsp; above 3.0</li>\r\n				<li>PhD History &ndash; at least an M.A. in History or any master&rsquo;s degree in humanities and social sciences.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>No. of students needed for enrollment for each program</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li>B.A. History &ndash; 45 students per intake</li>\r\n				<li>M.A. History &ndash; 20 students per intake</li>\r\n				<li>PhD History &ndash; subject to specialization of supervisors</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Career opportunities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>A person who has pursued our programs fits in many carriers. Some of them include;</p>\r\n\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li>iConsultancy work for public and private institutions</li>\r\n				<li>iiResearchers &ndash; e.g. investigative and historical researches</li>\r\n				<li>iiiMuseum curators &ndash; curators of history in museums</li>\r\n				<li>ivArchivists</li>\r\n				<li>vEducational officers in secondary schools and colleges</li>\r\n				<li>viUniversity lecturers</li>\r\n				<li>viiCultural officers in the government level at district, regional and ministerial levels</li>\r\n				<li>viiiJournalists and documentary producers &ndash; e.g. historical documentaries</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Other opportunities</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li>iInstitutional and company historians</li>\r\n				<li>iiCan work in different government organs and levels like administration, army, police and planning.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Collaboration with other institutes/departments</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>The Department of History has a long established collaboration with other international universities like</p>\r\n\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li>iBergen University of Health Sciences, Bergen, Norway</li>\r\n				<li>iiTexas Southern University, Texas, USA.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Department&rsquo;s projects that in a way benefit students</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>The Department is revising its curriculum to incorporate new approaches and programs that will involve students and lecturers the purpose being to increase practical learning to the students and make them more competitive in the current labor market.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Department&rsquo;s contributions to the nation and Africa from 1964 to the present.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>-It has produced many government and political parties&rsquo; leaders.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-It has produced many of the best history teachers and lecturers, curators and cultural officers</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-It has contributed to the emergence of Dar es Salaam School of Thought, an African historical perspective which has reduced the misinterpretation of African history.</p>\r\n\r\n			<p>-It has widened the scope and range of issues in historical and development researches.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Target Population for Department&rsquo;s Degree Program</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>-The Department degree programmes are open to all. It has an international character in its studentship, teaching and staff. For instance, reknown historians like Walter Rodney, John Iliffe and Terence Ranger were once its teaching staff.&nbsp; It also receives a substantial number of international students from bachelor to PhD degree level.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact</p>\r\n\r\n<p>P.O BOX 35040</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dar es Salaam</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tel : +255 22 2410397</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fax: +255 22 2410397</p>\r\n\r\n<p>E-mail: <a href="mailto:history@udsm.ac.tz">history@udsm.ac.tz</a></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>History </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Department of History</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Year of Establishment</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>1964, One of the oldest Departments of theUniversityofDar es Salaam.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Vision</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>To become an internationally recognized History Department and Centre for research, teaching, consultancy and publication.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:162.75pt">\r\n			<p>Mission</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top; width:301.5pt">\r\n			<p>To enable students to become best historically-minded individuals (informed decision makers and 