(143, 'philosophy-department', 'philosophy-department', '<p><strong>Philosophy and Religious Studies</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Department of Philosophy&nbsp;and Religious Studies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Philosophy is said to be &lsquo;the mother of all sciences&rsquo; as philosophical analysis and argumentation gives foundations for any other academic study and scientific knowledge. In most universities in the world and in the region, philosophical studies are considered of central importance, and strong programmes in philosophy have been developed to maintain this tradition of analytical reasoning. While across the world, philosophy is a very active field of study and research, the UDSM has been one of few main national universities in the region that do not have a full philosophy programme. In light of this background, this proposal seeks to fulfil this gap and put the UDSM back on the map of the universities which invest in intellectual development and encourages the birth of new ideas and critical analysis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Degree Program</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bachelor of Arts in philosophy and Ethics ( BA in Philosophy and Ethics)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The duration of the programme for a BA in Philosophy is three years, each consisting of two semesters. Each semester comprises of 15 weeks of teaching, equivalent to 30 lectures and 15 seminars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Structure of the Programme</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The BA in Philosophy programme will be offered by course work, examinations, tests, research, and seminars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Requirements into the Programme</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Requirement for entry into the BA Philosophy and Ethics program will be those set by the University and College ofHumanities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Direct Entry (Form six qualifications)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission in the BA philosophy program will require candidates to fulfill all requirements stipulated by the University in general and the College of Humanities. More specifically, a candidate will require two or more principal level passes in arts subjects to be admitted into the program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. Equivalent Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An appropriate diploma recognized by the senate of the University of Dar es Salaam, of not less than second-class, or credit standing. In particular holders of the following diplomas with their NACTE Code, shall be considered to be eligible to study Philosophy and Ethics:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p><strong>S/N</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p><strong>Title of Diploma</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p><strong>NACTE Code</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>1.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>Ordinary Diploma in Management and Teaching with Arts subjects</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>ODTLF01</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>2.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>Ordinary Diploma in Education with Arts Subjects</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>ODTLF02</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>3.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>Ordinary Diploma in Adult and Continuing Education with Arts Subjects</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>ODTLF03</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>4.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>Ordinary Diploma in Primary Teachers Education with Arts subjects</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="vertical-align:top">\r\n			<p>ODTLF04</p>\r\n			</td>\r\