me</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 8,500,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>6</td>\r\n			<td>Master of Science in Computer and IT Systems Engineering (MSc. in CITSE)</td>\r\n			<td>18 Months &ndash; Regular Programme&nbsp;<br />\r\n			24 Months &ndash; Evening Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 8,500,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>7</td>\r\n			<td>Master of Engineering Management (MEM)</td>\r\n			<td>24 Months &ndash; Evening Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 6,375,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:800px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>SN.</th>\r\n			<th>PHD PROGRAMME NAME</th>\r\n			<th>DURATION</th>\r\n			<th>FEES</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Telecommunications Engineering</td>\r\n			<td>3 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Electronics Engineering and Information Technology</td>\r\n			<td>3 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Computer Science (PhD in CS) by Thesis</td>\r\n			<td>3 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Computer Engineering and IT by Thesis</td>\r\n			<td>3 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Health Informatics (PhD in HI) by Thesis</td>\r\n			<td>3 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>6</td>\r\n			<td>Doctor of Philosophy in Computer and IT Systems Engineering (PhD. in CITSE)</td>\r\n			<td>4 Years</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 13,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Requirements for Postgraduate Programme</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Postgraduate Diploma in Electronics Engineering and Information Technology</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Advanced diploma or equivalent in Engineering in relevant field from a recognised college, or a pass degree in Engineering in the relevant field from a recognized University</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MSc. in Computer Science</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The minimum admission qualification is Lower Second Class in BSc. degree in Informatics or related discipline from a recognized University, or a Postgraduate Diploma in Informatics or related discipline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MSc. in Health Informatics</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The minimum admission qualification is Lower Second Class in BSc. degree in Informatics or related discipline or BSc. degree in Health Sciences or related qualifications, with an overall grade of B or higher. In addition, a minimum of one year work experience is required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MSc. in Information System Management</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Direct Entry Qualification:</strong>&nbsp;An undergraduate degree in Information Systems Management or a related field from a recognized institution with at least a Lower Second class with GPA of at least 2.7 out of 5.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Equivalent Entry Qualification:&nbsp;</strong>Advanced Diploma in relevant and respective field with at least Lower Second Class award OR Undergraduate Degree with at least a pass in related field PLUS a Postgraduate Diploma in a relevant and respective field from a recognized institution certified by TCU with at least an Upper Second Class award (GPA of at least 3.5 out of 5).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>MSc. in Computer and IT Systems Engineering</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Direct Entry Qualification:</strong>&nbsp;UQF Level 8 with background in IT related undergraduate Programmes or Electrical Engineering related Programmes which include IT courses with at least a Second Class degree with minimum GPA of at least 2.7 out of 5 from a respected institution recognized by TCU or equivalent.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Equivalent Entry Qualification:</strong>&nbsp;A Postgraduate Diploma in IT related Programmes or Electrical Engineering related Programmes which includes IT courses from a respected institution recognized by TCU or equivalent with at least an upper second class B+ award with minimum GPA of 3.5 out of 5. Candidates with equivalent qualifications must also possess at least Ordinary Secondary School certificate with principal passes in Physics and Mathematics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PhD in; Computer Science/Computer Engineering and IT/Health Informatics</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The student should be a holder of relevant Master degree of the University of Dar es Salaam or any other recognized and accredited University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PhD in Computer and IT Systems Engineering</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The student should satisfy the general University minimum requirements plus the following additional requirements: Master&rsquo;s degree in IT related Programmes which includes IT courses with at least an Upper Second Class degree with minimum GPA of 3.0 out of 5.0 from a respected institution recognized by TCU or equivalent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) in Telecommunications Engineering or in Electronics Engineering and Information Technology</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The minimum qualification for admission to the programme is a relevant Masters degree from the University of Dar es Salaam or any other recognized institution.</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Table 1:</strong>&nbsp;A list of Postgraduates Programmes and Fees Structure</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:800px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>SN.</th>\r\n			<th>DIPLOMA PROGRAMME NAME</th>\r\n			<th>DURATION</th>\r\n			<th>FEES</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1.</td>\r\n			<td>Postgraduate Diploma in Electronics Engineering and Information Technology</td>\r\n			<td>1 Year</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 4,250,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2.</td>\r\n			<td>Postg