(200, 'Non-Degree', 'Non-Degree', '<p><strong>Table 1:</strong>&nbsp;A list of Non-Degree Programmes and Fees Structure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:800px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>SN.</th>\r\n			<th>PROGRAMME NAME</th>\r\n			<th>DURATION</th>\r\n			<th>FEES</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>Certificate in Computer Science (Cert. in CS),</td>\r\n			<td>1 Year , Evening Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 800,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>Diploma in Computer Science (Dipl. in CS)</td>\r\n			<td>2 Years Duration, Evening and Regular Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 2,000,000/</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Qualifications for Certificate in Computer Science</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category A: Direct Entry</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or East African Certificate of Education (E.A.C.A) &ndash; O-level with at least a pass in four approved subjects including Mathematics.</li>\r\n	<li>OR An Advanced Certificate of Secondary Education with at least two subsidiary passes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category B: Equivalent Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other additional qualifications (such as Certificate or diploma in relevant field or ICT industrial experience of not less than 2 years) that demonstrate the candidate&rsquo;s ability to undertake the Programmes may also be considered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Qualifications for Diploma in Computer Science</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category A: Direct Entry</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or equivalent with passes in at least four approved subjects including Mathematics, and one of the following combinations of passes in the Advanced Certificate of Secondary Education Examination or equivalent:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Three Subsidiary passes in Computer Science, Advanced Mathematics, Basic Applied Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, Economics, Commerce, Geography, Biology or Accountancy.</li>\r\n	<li>OR one principal level pass at least grade &lsquo;C&rsquo; or better in any of the subjects listed in (i) above.</li>\r\n	<li>OR one principal level pass and a subsidiary pass in any of the subjects listed in (i) above.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a Certificate in Computer Science with an average GPA of at least 2.7 out of 5.0 from recognized institution.</li>\r\n	<li>OR any Bachelor Degree from recognized institution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category B: Equivalent Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or equivalent with passes in at least four approved subjects and one of the following qualifications:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Certificate in Computer Science (or related field) with an average GPA of at least 3.0 out of 5.0 or a Diploma at a good standing from recognized institution.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a qualification of an equivalent standard awarded by recognized professional bodies such as the National Board of Accountants and Auditors and the Business Education Council.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a Form VI certificate with at least two subsidiaries in the subjects listed in (a) (i) above plus at least two years industrial experience in ICT.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>Table 1:</strong>&nbsp;A list of Non-Degree Programmes and Fees Structure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:800px">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th>SN.</th>\r\n			<th>PROGRAMME NAME</th>\r\n			<th>DURATION</th>\r\n			<th>FEES</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>Certificate in Computer Science (Cert. in CS),</td>\r\n			<td>1 Year , Evening Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 800,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>Diploma in Computer Science (Dipl. in CS)</td>\r\n			<td>2 Years Duration, Evening and Regular Programme</td>\r\n			<td>TZS 2,000,000/</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Qualifications for Certificate in Computer Science</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category A: Direct Entry</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or East African Certificate of Education (E.A.C.A) &ndash; O-level with at least a pass in four approved subjects including Mathematics.</li>\r\n	<li>OR An Advanced Certificate of Secondary Education with at least two subsidiary passes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category B: Equivalent Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other additional qualifications (such as Certificate or diploma in relevant field or ICT industrial experience of not less than 2 years) that demonstrate the candidate&rsquo;s ability to undertake the Programmes may also be considered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Qualifications for Diploma in Computer Science</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category A: Direct Entry</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or equivalent with passes in at least four approved subjects including Mathematics, and one of the following combinations of passes in the Advanced Certificate of Secondary Education Examination or equivalent:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Three Subsidiary passes in Computer Science, Advanced Mathematics, Basic Applied Mathematics, Physics, Chemistry, Economics, Commerce, Geography, Biology or Accountancy.</li>\r\n	<li>OR one principal level pass at least grade &lsquo;C&rsquo; or better in any of the subjects listed in (i) above.</li>\r\n	<li>OR one principal level pass and a subsidiary pass in any of the subjects listed in (i) above.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a Certificate in Computer Science with an average GPA of at least 2.7 out of 5.0 from recognized institution.</li>\r\n	<li>OR any Bachelor Degree from recognized institution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Category B: Equivalent Qualifications</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate of Secondary Education Examination (C.S.E.E.) or equivalent with passes in at least four approved subjects and one of the following qualifications:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Certificate in Computer Science (or related field) with an average GPA of at least 3.0 out of 5.0 or a Diploma at a good standing from recognized institution.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a qualification of an equivalent standard awarded by recognized professional bodies such as the National Board of Accountants and Auditors and the Business Education Council.</li>\r\n	<li>OR a Form VI certificate with at least two subsidiaries in the subjects listed in (a) (i) above plus at least two years industrial experience in ICT.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', NULL, '', '/colleges/coict/non-degree', '2017-11-23 17:49:46', 1, 4, NULL),
(201, 'udsm Admission', 'udsm Admission', '<p><strong>Welcome,</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Selection&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/?q=node/915">Results can be downloaded here</a>!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A renowned and highly ranked University in Africa, the University of Dar es Salaam stands as the most prestigious University in Tanzania. It is a comprehensive University that caters for the entire East and Southern African region, offering a wide range of academic disciplines at both undergraduate and postgraduate levels. The University of Dar es Salaam is home to most qualified and internationally acknowledged scholars in Africa. By this announcement, applications are now open to qualified candidates from Tanzania, the East and Southern African region and beyond, who wish to pursue undergraduate degree programmes for the academic year 2017/2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University of Dar es salaam (UDSM) offers various academic programmes leading to the award of certificates, diplomas, and degrees. A total of 88 Undergraduate Degree Programmes are offered at various academic units of the University. &nbsp;You may download the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/sites/default/files/Admission%20Handbook%202017_2018%20Final%20Updated.pdf">UDSM Admission Procedures Guidebook</a>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/"><u>www.udsm.ac.tz</u></a>&nbsp;(Undergraduates section) for information about all programmes and their requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applications for admission are invited from qualified candidates wishing to pursue various undergraduate degree programmes for the academic year 2017/2018. All requisite information and guidelines to take the applicant through the application stages are provided from&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong><em>Instructions</em></strong>&nbsp;tab.&nbsp;<strong>Applicants are reminded</strong>&nbsp;to register their&nbsp;<strong>names&nbsp;</strong>as they appear in their<strong>&nbsp;O &amp; A level certificates</strong>; likewise their&nbsp;<strong>index numbers</strong>&nbsp;where prompted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All Direct applicants with Foreign Certificates should first present their certificates to the National Examinations Council of Tanzania (NECTA) for verification. They will in turn be given letters showing NECTA equivalent&nbsp;grades, copies of which should also&nbsp;be uploaded together with other certifcates. Further information on NECTA verification can be obtained from www.necta.go.tz.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equivalent applicants are advised to obtain a special unique number from National Council for Technical Education (NACTE) which will be required when applying in the system. For further&nbsp;information&nbsp;about NACTE verification process please consult them at www.nacte.go.tz.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kindly take note that the deadline for applications is&nbsp;<strong>30<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;August, 2017.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For any Problem please &nbsp;use the contacts below</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong><br />\r\n+255 22 241 0751</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Admission Office&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n+255 22 241 0544<br />\r\ndus@admin.udsm.ac.tz<br />\r\n<strong>Technical&nbsp; Support</strong><br />\r\n+255 71 621 6308<br />\r\n+255 62 932 4903<br />\r\n+255 76 553 7512&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nsupport@udsm.ac.tz<br />\r\n<strong>Payment Issues</strong><br />\r\nmalipo@admission.ac.tz</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>Welcome,</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Undergraduate Selection&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/?q=node/915">Results can be downloaded here</a>!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A renowned and highly ranked University in Africa, the University of Dar es Salaam stands as the most prestigious University in Tanzania. It is a comprehensive University that caters for the entire East and Southern African region, offering a wide range of academic disciplines at both undergraduate and postgraduate levels. The University of Dar es Salaam is home to most qualified and internationally acknowledged scholars in Africa. By this announcement, applications are now open to qualified candidates from Tanzania, the East and Southern African region and beyond, who wish to pursue undergraduate degree programmes for the academic year 2017/2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University of Dar es salaam (UDSM) offers various academic programmes leading to the award of certificates, diplomas, and degrees. A total of 88 Undergraduate Degree Programmes are offered at various academic units of the University. &nbsp;You may download the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/sites/default/files/Admission%20Handbook%202017_2018%20Final%20Updated.pdf">UDSM Admission Procedures Guidebook</a>&nbsp;from&nbsp;<a href="https://www.udsm.ac.tz/"><u>www.udsm.ac.tz</u></a>&nbsp;(Undergraduates section) for information about all programmes and their requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Applications for admission are invited from qualified candidates wishing to pursue various undergraduate degree programmes for the academic year 2017/2018. All requisite information and guidelines to take the applicant through the application stages are provided from&nbsp;the&nbsp;<strong><em>Instructions</em></strong>&nbsp;tab.&nbsp;<strong>Applicants are reminded</strong>&nbsp;to register their&nbsp;<strong>names&nbsp;</strong>as they appear in their<strong>&nbsp;O &amp; A level certificates</strong>; likewise their&nbsp;<strong>index numbers</strong>&nbsp;where prompted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All Direct applicants with Foreign Certificates should first present their certificates to the National Examinations Council of Tanzania (NECTA) for verification. They will in turn be given letters showing NECTA equivalent&nbsp;grades, copies of which should also&nbsp;be uploaded together with other certifcates. Further information on NECTA verification can be obtained from www.necta.go.tz.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equivalent applicants are advised to obtain a special unique number from National Council for Technical Education (NACTE) which will be required when applying in the system. For further&nbsp;information&nbsp;about NACTE verification process please consult them at www.nacte.go.tz.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kindly take note that the deadline for applications is&nbsp;<strong>30<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;August, 2017.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For any Problem please &nbsp;use the contacts below</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong><br />\r\n+255 22 241 0751</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Admission Office&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n+255 22 241 0544<br />\r\ndus@admin.udsm.ac.tz<br />\r\n<strong>Technical&nbsp; Support</strong><br />\r\n+255 71 621 6308<br />\r\n+255 62 932 4903<br />\r\n+255 76 553 7512&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nsupport@udsm.ac.tz<br />\r\n<strong>Payment Issues</strong><br />\r\nmalipo@admission.ac.tz</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', '/colleges/coict/udsm-admission', '2017-11-24 06:05:51', 1, 4, NULL),
(202, 'Deadlines', 'Deadlines', '<p><strong>NEW APPLICANTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stage 1: Registration for an admission account:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Register for an account in our system through the button (register).<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Note: to register for an account in the admission system you will need to supply the following details:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First name</li>\r\n	<li>Surname</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Email Address</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Mobile Telephone Number</strong></li>\r\n	<li>To finalize registration you will need to put in a&nbsp;password of your choice that you will use whenever you wish to log into the admission&nbsp;system.</li>\r\n	<li>And lastly fill in the characters&nbsp;<em>captcha</em>&nbsp;as will be shown in the page, i.e.&nbsp;<em>Captcha</em>&nbsp;then click register button at the bottom to register for an account. &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are successfully registered, then the system will send an email to your email address, please log into your email account to activate your admission account.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Use the link sent into your email to log into our Admission system.<br />\r\n	<strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;at this stage.&nbsp;<strong>Your username is</strong>: your email address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Your Password is</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp; the password you supplied</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>NEW APPLICANTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stage 1: Registration for an admission account:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Register for an account in our system through the button (register).<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Note: to register for an account in the admission system you will need to supply the following details:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First name</li>\r\n	<li>Surname</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Email Address</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Mobile Telephone Number</strong></li>\r\n	<li>To finalize registration you will need to put in a&nbsp;password of your choice that you will use whenever you wish to log into the admission&nbsp;system.</li>\r\n	<li>And lastly fill in the characters&nbsp;<em>captcha</em>&nbsp;as will be shown in the page, i.e.&nbsp;<em>Captcha</em>&nbsp;then click register button at the bottom to register for an account. &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are successfully registered, then the system will send an email to your email address, please log into your email account to activate your admission account.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Use the link sent into your email to log into our Admission system.<br />\r\n	<strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;at this stage.&nbsp;<strong>Your username is</strong>: your email address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>Your Password is</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp; the password you supplied</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', '/colleges/coict/deadlines', '2017-11-24 06:23:25', 1, 4, NULL),
(203, 'Mission & Vision', 'Dhima  & Dira', '<p>UDSM Vision</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;to become a reputable world-class university that is responsive to national, regional and global development needs through engagement in dynamic knowledge creation and application.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDSM Mission</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;the unrelenting pursuit of scholarly and strategic research, education, training and public service directed at attainment of equitable and sustainable socio-economic development of Tanzania and the rest of Africa.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guiding Theme</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The focus of the University of Dar es Salaam activities during the period 2006/ 07 - 2010/11, shall be guided by the following theme: &quot;Enhanced quality outputs in teaching, research and public service&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDSM Values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Towards achieving its Vision and fulfilling its Mission, the University of Dar es Salaam subscribes to the following Values:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Academic excellence by ensuring that the pursuit of academic excellence in teaching, research and service to the public is well recognised and forms an important part of the academic and organisational life of the institution.</li>\r\n	<li>Academic integrity by ensuring that all the academic outputs are produced in line with international standards of academic integrity.</li>\r\n	<li>Academic freedom by upholding the spirit of free and critical thought and enquiry, through the tolerance of a diversity of beliefs and understanding, as well as fostering open exchange of ideas and knowledge amongst the staff and/or students.</li>\r\n	<li>&ldquo;unrelenting pursuit of scholarly and strategic research, education, training and public service directed at the attainment of equitable and sustainable socio-economic developmentof Tanzania and the rest of Africa.&rdquo;</li>\r\n	<li>Internationalisation through participation in the regional and global world of scholarship, by being receptive and responsive to issues within the international environment, as well as enrolling an increasing number of international students.</li>\r\n	<li>Professional and ethical standards by upholding the highest professional standards and ethical behaviour, and through openness, honesty, tolerance and respect for the individual in all disciplines.</li>\r\n	<li>Social responsibility by promoting an awareness of, and providing leadership to respond to, the issues and problems facing society with a view to ultimately solving and alleviating them.</li>\r\n	<li>Developmental responsibility by ensuring that most of the research conducted has an immediate or long-term impact.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Teaching and learning by creating a holistic teaching and learning environment which is student centred, providing students with social, cultural and recreational opportunities that will facilitate the full realisation of their potential for academic and personal growth.</li>\r\n	<li>Institutional autonomy characterised by self-governing structures guided by the University&rsquo;s Council and greater independence of action, while being responsive to societal and development needs or to what is prescribed by the relevant legal instruments.</li>\r\n	<li>Public accountability by ensuring transparent decision making and open review, as well as the full participation of stakeholders in the development of the institution and in major policy shifts.</li>\r\n	<li>Equity and social justice by ensuring equal opportunity and non-discrimination on the basis of personal, ethnic, religious, gender or other social characteristics.</li>\r\n	<li>Strategic planning culture by inculcating it at all levels in the University.</li>\r\n	<li>Research relevance by ensuring that research addresses relevant national or societal problems.</li>\r\n	<li>ICT use of ICT by application of ICT in the enhancement of academic delivery and management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>UDSM Vision</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;To become a reputable world-class university that is responsive to national, regional and global development needs through engagement in dynamic knowledge creation and application.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDSM Mission</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;The unrelenting pursuit of scholarly and strategic research, education, training and public service directed at attainment of equitable and sustainable socio-economic development of Tanzania and the rest of Africa.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Guiding Theme</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The focus of the University of Dar es Salaam activities during the period 2006/ 07 - 2010/11, shall be guided by the following theme: &quot;Enhanced quality outputs in teaching, research and public service&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDSM Values</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Towards achieving its Vision and fulfilling its Mission, the University of Dar es Salaam subscribes to the following Values:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Academic excellence by ensuring that the pursuit of academic excellence in teaching, research and service to the public is well recognised and forms an important part of the academic and organisational life of the institution.</li>\r\n	<li>Academic integrity by ensuring that all the academic outputs are produced in line with international standards of academic integrity.</li>\r\n	<li>Academic freedom by upholding the spirit of free and critical thought and enquiry, through the tolerance of a diversity of beliefs and understanding, as well as fostering open exchange of ideas and knowledge amongst the staff and/or students.</li>\r\n	<li>&ldquo;unrelenting pursuit of scholarly and strategic research, education, training and public service directed at the attainment of equitable and sustainable socio-economic developmentof Tanzania and the rest of Africa.&rdquo;</li>\r\n	<li>Internationalisation through participation in the regional and global world of scholarship, by being receptive and responsive to issues within the international environment, as well as enrolling an increasing number of international students.</li>\r\n	<li>Professional and ethical standards by upholding the highest professional standards and ethical behaviour, and through openness, honesty, tolerance and respect for the individual in all disciplines.</li>\r\n	<li>Social responsibility by promoting an awareness of, and providing leadership to respond to, the issues and problems facing society with a view to ultimately solving and alleviating them.</li>\r\n	<li>Developmental responsibility by ensuring that most of the research conducted has an immediate or long-term impact.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Teaching and learning by creating a holistic teaching and learning environment which is student centred, providing students with social, cultural and recreational opportunities that will facilitate the full realisation of their potential for academic and personal growth.</li>\r\n	<li>Institutional autonomy characterised by self-governing structures guided by the University&rsquo;s Council and greater independence of action, while being responsive to societal and development needs or to what is prescribed by the relevant legal instruments.</li>\r\n	<li>Public accountability by ensuring transparent decision making and open review, as well as the full participation of stakeholders in the development of the institution and in major policy shifts.</li>\r\n	<li>Equity and social justice by ensuring equal opportunity and non-discrimination on the basis of personal, ethnic, religious, gender or other social characteristics.</li>\r\n	<li>Strategic planning culture by inculcating it at all levels in the University.</li>\r\n	<li>Research relevance by ensuring that research addresses relevant national or societal problems.</li>\r\n	<li>ICT use of ICT by application of ICT in the enhancement of academic delivery and management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', NULL, '', '/mission-and-vision', '2017-11-24 08:26:10', 1, NULL, NULL),
(204, 'Postgraduate Admission', 'Postgraduate Admission', '<p>Announcement of Postgraduate Admissions for 2015/2016 Academic Year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University of Dar es Salaam would like to announce that the following applicants have been selected to join various postgraduate programmes for the 2015/2016 academic year. The orientation week and registration processes for new students at UDSM Mwalimu J.K. Nyerere Main Campus will start on Monday12th October 2015 as stipulated in the admission letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those applicants selected for admission into the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS), Dar es Salaam University College of Education (DUCE) and Mkwawa University College of Education (MUCE) should report directly at the respective campuses in Zanzibar, Chang&rsquo;ombe and Iringa on the same date. Joining instructions and admission letters should be collected at the UDSM Mwalimu J.K. Nyerere Main Campus, IMS, DUCE and MUCE depending on where one is admitted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>***Please click the link below to view selected applicants to join various postgraduate programmes for the 2015/2016 academic year ***</p>\r\n', '<p>Announcement of Postgraduate Admissions for 2015/2016 Academic Year</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The University of Dar es Salaam would like to announce that the following applicants have been selected to join various postgraduate programmes for the 2015/2016 academic year. The orientation week and registration processes for new students at UDSM Mwalimu J.K. Nyerere Main Campus will start on Monday12th October 2015 as stipulated in the admission letters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For those applicants selected for admission into the Institute of Marine Sciences (IMS), Dar es Salaam University College of Education (DUCE) and Mkwawa University College of Education (MUCE) should report directly at the respective campuses in Zanzibar, Chang&rsquo;ombe and Iringa on the same date. Joining instructions and admission letters should be collected at the UDSM Mwalimu J.K. Nyerere Main Campus, IMS, DUCE and MUCE depending on where one is admitted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>***Please click the link below to view selected applicants to join various postgraduate programmes for the 2015/2016 academic year ***</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', '/postgraduate-admission', '2017-11-27 06:55:24', 2, NULL, NULL);
