(253, 'User Training', 'User Training', '<p><strong>Information Literacy Training Programmes</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em><u>Participants</u></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All Postgraduate and Undergraduate students are encouraged to attend this course</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Academic Staff of all levels are also encouraged to attend</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><u><strong>Course Content</strong></u></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(i) Using Online Public Access Catalogue (OPAC): Simple and advanced search techniques.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(ii) Internet for learning and research: Internet search engines and Information Gateways</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iii) Electronic Resources and Services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(iv) Evaluating and Citing Electronic Information</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(v)UDSM Virtual Library: resources and services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(vi) UDSM Library Website as a Communication Tool</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;<em><u> </u></em><strong><em><u>Venue</u></em>:&nbsp; </strong>Library Cluster Room</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; <u><em><strong>Time:</strong></em></u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Courses will be conducted as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monday to Friday:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 9.00am - 12.00 noon</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.00pm&nbsp; -&nbsp; 5.00pm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saturdays on request from Faculty members:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 9.00am - 12.00 noon</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em><u>Registration:</u></em>&nbsp; </strong>Please register for respective sessions at the check point of the Reference and Document Delivery Section, Second Floor UDSM Main Library</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Training Capacity:&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>25 to 30 students per session</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u><em><strong>Contact Information:</strong></