(49, 'MSc. Marine Sciences (MASC) by Coursework and Dissertation (MSc MASC)', 'MSc. Marine Sciences (MASC) by Coursework and Dissertation (MSc MASC)', 'msc.-marine-sciences-(masc)-by-coursework-and-dissertation-(msc-masc)', '24 Months', 'Miezi 24', '<p>At the end of the MSc in Marine Sciences by Coursework and Dissertation programme students are expected to be able to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Demonstrate intellectual capacities, critical faculties, transferable skills and knowledge to investigate solutions for conserving and ensuring long term sustainability of marine and coastal resources.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Exhibit an interdisciplinary understanding of the marine and coastal resource environments and the need for interdisciplinary and multisector approaches to their management.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critically analyze marine and coastal policy frameworks affecting the management of coastal and marine resources.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Apply remote sensing and geographical information systems as tools for informed decisions regarding utilization and management of coastal and marine resource in a sustainable manner.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assess long term sustainability of activities in the marine and coastal areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '<p>At the end of the MSc in Marine Sciences by Coursework and Dissertation programme students are expected to be able to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Demonstrate intellectual capacities, critical faculties, transferable skills and knowledge to investigate solutions for conserving and ensuring long term sustainability of marine and coastal resources.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Exhibit an interdisciplinary understanding of the marine and coastal resource environments and the need for interdisciplinary and multisector approaches to their management.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Critically analyze marine and coastal policy frameworks affecting the management of coastal and marine resources.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Apply remote sensing and geographical information systems as tools for informed decisions regarding utilization and management of coastal and marine resource in a sustainable manner.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Assess long term sustainability of activities in the marine and coastal areas</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 23, '<p>An undergraduate degree from any TCU recognized university with background in science subjects relevant to marine sciences such as physics, chemistry, biology and geology, with a GPA of 2.7 (B grade) or higher. Applicants with equivalent qualifications may also be considered.</p>\r\n', NULL, 2, 5, 1, '2017-11-13 13:05:34'),
