(3, 'PREPARATION OF THE DAR ES SALAAM CITY ENVIRONMENT OUTLOOK ', 'PREPARATION OF THE DAR ES SALAAM CITY ENVIRONMENT OUTLOOK ', 'preparation-of-the-dar-es-salaam-city-environment-outlook', 22, '<p>This assignment was sponsored by the Vice President&rsquo;s Office, Division of Environment. This work contributes to the development of the National Environment Outlook, which is in line with the Environmental Management Act (EMA) Cap 191, and the National Strategy for Growth and Reduction of Poverty (NSGRP) that requires preparation of periodic reports on the state of the environment. The general objective of Dar es Salaam City Environment Outlook was to collect and provide data that will identify key environmental issues for informed decision making in the Dar es Salaam City.</p>\r\n', '<p>This assignment was sponsored by the Vice President&rsquo;s Office, Division of Environment. This work contributes to the development of the National Environment Outlook, which is in line with the Environmental Management Act (EMA) Cap 191, and the National Strategy for Growth and Reduction of Poverty (NSGRP) that requires preparation of periodic reports on the state of the environment. The general objective of Dar es Salaam City Environment Outlook was to collect and provide data that will identify key environmental issues for informed decision making in the Dar es Salaam City.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. xyz', '<p>Prof xyx</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. xyz</p>\r\n', 'USAID', 'USAID', 'Oct 1, 2017', 'Feb 1, 2018', 1, 'preparation-of-the-dar-es-salaam-city-environment-outlook'),
(4, 'ECONOMIC POTENTIALS, PHYTOCHEMICAL EVALUATION AND GENETIC CHARACTERIZATION OF NEGLECTED AND UNDERUTILIZED EAST AND WEST AFRICAN PLANT SPECIES', 'ECONOMIC POTENTIALS, PHYTOCHEMICAL EVALUATION AND GENETIC CHARACTERIZATION OF NEGLECTED AND UNDERUTILIZED EAST AND WEST AFRICAN PLANT SPECIES', 'economic-potentials,-phytochemical-evaluation-and-genetic-characterization-of-neglected-and-underutilized-east-and-west-african-plant-species', 22, '<p>This is a two years on-going research project undertaken in the East and West regions of Africa (Tanzania, Uganda and Nigeria). It is a practical response to realization that several plants growing commonly in East and West Africa recognized as traditional foods and medicine are underutilized and poorly studied continued to instigate the search for natural, potent and affordable plant-derived therapies.</p>\r\n', '<p>This is a two years on-going research project undertaken in the East and West regions of Africa (Tanzania, Uganda and Nigeria). It is a practical response to realization that several plants growing commonly in East and West Africa recognized as traditional foods and medicine are underutilized and poorly studied continued to instigate the search for natural, potent and affordable plant-derived therapies.</p>\r\n', 'Prof. ABC', '<p>Prof XYZ</p>\r\n', 'SIDA-SAREC', 'SIDA-SAREC', 'Apr 1, 2014', 'Nov 30, 2017', 1, 'economic-potentials,-phytochemical-evaluation-and-genetic-characterization-of-neglected-and-underutilized-east-and-west-african-plant-species');
